HEADWORD: Mastoid
<hw>Mas"toid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>masto`s</grk> the breast + <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form: cf. F.
<ets>masto⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Resembling the nipple or the breast; -- applied specifically to a
process of the temporal bone behind the ear.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Pertaining to, or in the region of, the mastoid process;
mastoidal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

